To calculate the Return on Assets (ROA), we follow the formula:

ROA = (Net Income / Average Total Assets) x 100%

Step 1: Identify Net Income (Net Profit) for the period
- From the income statement, Net Profit = -1,175,062.19

Step 2: Determine Total Assets at the beginning and end of the period
- Beginning Total Assets (2023-12-31): 13,000,000.00
- Ending Total Assets (2024-01-29): 14,879,933.86

Step 3: Calculate Average Total Assets
Average = (Beginning Total Assets + Ending Total Assets) / 2
= (13,000,000.00 + 14,879,933.86) / 2
= 27,879,933.86 / 2
= 13,939,966.93

Step 4: Calculate ROA
ROA = (Net Profit / Average Total Assets) x 100%
= (-1,175,062.19 / 13,939,966.93) x 100%
≈ -0.08436 x 100%
≈ -8.44%
